# ⚓ ANCHOR: affinescript
# Canonical authority and identity statement for the AffineScript repository.
#
# First written 2026-04-10 during the Manhattan Recovery session that realigned
# the language scope from bot-drift back to user intent. This ANCHOR is
# retroactive: the project predates the ANCHOR.a2ml convention, and a full
# .machine_readable/ suite upgrade (anchors/, CLADE.a2ml, contractiles/,
# agent_instructions/, integrations/, top-level .contractile files) is deferred
# as separate work — see STATE.a2ml [deferred-upgrade].

id: "org.hyperpolymath.affinescript"
version: "0.2.0"
clade: "language"
status: "active-recovery"

# ─── Thesis (canonical scope statement) ───────────────────────────────────────
# This thesis is authoritative. Code must conform to it, not the reverse.
# See [feedback_language_scope_in_thesis.md] in the estate memory store.

thesis:
  one-sentence: >
    AffineScript is JavaScript-ergonomic correctness: the developer experience
    of the -script family (TypeScript, ReScript, PureScript) raised to a higher
    correctness floor through a small, deliberately chosen set of advanced
    types, compiling to Typed WASM.

  ergonomic-target: "closer to JavaScript than ReScript in experience"

  design-principle: >
    Ergonomics first. The type system defaults must be sensible so most code
    reads like modern JavaScript while correctness is enforced at compile time.
    A feature earns its place only if it makes correct code easier to write.

  in-scope:
    - phantom-types                # free via generics
    - immutable-by-default         # matches ReScript/Elm/Grain/JS `const`
    - row-polymorphism             # PureScript/Elm pattern
    - full-type-inference          # HM-style; quantities at signatures, inferred in function bodies
    - sound-type-system            # table stakes; three bugs currently open
    - effect-tracking              # TRACKING only; handlers deferred — see ADR-004
    - affine-types                 # the headline novelty; no -script has this
    - refinement-types-decidable   # soft commitment, decidable fragment only, no SMT

  out-of-scope:
    - linear-strict-types          # subsumed by affine; bot scope-creep, being removed
    - full-dependent-types         # deferred to sibling Typed WASM project
    - tropical-types               # deferred to sibling Typed WASM project
    - algebraic-effect-handlers    # documented extension point, not current feature
    - unbounded-refinement-types   # decidability boundary; SMT not required
    - units-of-measure             # Typed WASM project
    - shape-indexed-vectors        # Typed WASM project

  exception-model:
    # Option A+: exceptions are the one degenerate algebraic-effect case that
    # works cleanly with affine types because resume is never called.
    - "try/catch/finally grammar already present in parser.mly:542-587"
    - "wiring through interp + codegen is Phase 1.5 work"
    - "richer effect handlers are a documented extension point, see ADR-004"

# ─── Authoritative documents ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

authorities:
  scope-statement:
    - ".machine_readable/6a2/META.a2ml (ADRs)"
    - "~/Desktop/Frontier_Programming_Practices_AffineScript/AI.a2ml (v2.0)"

  human-guide:
    - "~/Desktop/Frontier_Programming_Practices_AffineScript/Human_Programming_Guide.adoc (v2.0)"

  architecture-decisions:
    - "ADR-001: Split-Γ canonical (META.a2ml)"
    - "ADR-002: Scaled Let rule (META.a2ml)"
    - "ADR-003: L-to-R evaluation order (META.a2ml)"
    # ADR-004: algebraic effect handlers extension point — pending
    # ADR-005: language scope statement (narrow thesis) — pending
    # ADR-006: exceptions as degenerate effect handler — pending

# ─── Relationships ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

parents:
  - id: "org.hyperpolymath.nextgen-languages"
    relationship: "submodule-of-monorepo"

siblings:
  - id: "org.hyperpolymath.typed-wasm"
    relationship: "compile-target-primary"
    note: >
      Typed WASM is AffineScript's primary compile target. It is designed as a
      standalone project that can serve other languages beyond AffineScript.
      Dependent types, tropical types, units of measure, and shape-indexed
      vectors all live there, not here.

  - id: "org.hyperpolymath.julia"
    relationship: "compile-target-secondary"
    note: "Julia backend for scientific computing use cases."

# ─── Realignment history ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

realignment-history:
  - date: "2026-04-10"
    event: "manhattan-recovery"
    session-type: "scope-recovery"
    trigger: >
      User acknowledged that bot scope creep had silently added linear types,
      dependent types, and algebraic effect handler ambitions that were never
      requested. The cascade of fixes each caused new problems, and the codebase
      had drifted from being a conceptual mirror of the author's intent.

    summary: >
      Scope narrowed from bot-drifted 12+ features back to the original 8-item
      thesis. Three ADRs adopted. Four soundness bugs identified and logged.
      Two estate-wide feedback memories saved. Desktop Frontier guides rewritten
      from defensive v1.0 drafts to positive v2.0 scope statements. Option A+
      chosen for effects (tracking + exceptions via existing try/catch grammar +
      documented extension point for future handlers). Inference form (a) chosen
      (quantities at signatures, inferred in bodies). Simplest module system
      chosen (one-file-per-module, flat namespace, no functors).

    changed:
      - "thesis (narrowed and made authoritative)"
      - "scope (8 features, not 12+)"
      - "soundness posture (BUG-001 through BUG-004 logged)"
      - "effect-handler posture (Option A+, exceptions via existing grammar)"
      - "authority structure (this ANCHOR created, thesis lives here and in META.a2ml)"
      - "documentation (Desktop guides v2.0 replacing v1.0)"

    references:
      - "META.a2ml [adr] ADR-001 split-gamma"
      - "META.a2ml [adr] ADR-002 scaled-let"
      - "META.a2ml [adr] ADR-003 lr-eval"
      - "STATE.a2ml [open-bug] BUG-001 omega-let-smuggles-linear"
      - "STATE.a2ml [open-bug] BUG-002 zero-let-erasure"
      - "STATE.a2ml [open-bug] BUG-003 eval-list-right-to-left"
      - "STATE.a2ml [open-bug] BUG-004 lambda-captures-untracked"
      - "~/.claude/projects/-var-mnt-eclipse-repos/memory/feedback_bot_scope_creep_free_variant.md"
      - "~/.claude/projects/-var-mnt-eclipse-repos/memory/feedback_language_scope_in_thesis.md"
      - "~/.claude/projects/-var-mnt-eclipse-repos/memory/feedback_completion_vs_behavioural_coverage.md"
      - "~/Desktop/Frontier_Programming_Practices_AffineScript/AI.a2ml (v2.0)"
      - "~/Desktop/Frontier_Programming_Practices_AffineScript/Human_Programming_Guide.adoc (v2.0)"

# ─── Notes on retroactive status ──────────────────────────────────────────────

notes: >
  This is the first ANCHOR.a2ml written for AffineScript. The repository
  predates the ANCHOR convention and predates significant portions of the
  current hyperpolymath .machine_readable/ suite (CLADE.a2ml, contractiles/
  as a .machine_readable/ subdirectory, agent_instructions/, integrations/,
  and top-level .contractile instance files). The existing root-level
  contractiles/ directory contains 5 of the 7 current contractile types
  (dust, k9, lust, must, trust — missing adjust and intend).

  A full upgrade to the current canonical suite is deferred as separate work.
  See STATE.a2ml [deferred-upgrade] for the itemised list. The minimum captured
  in this first ANCHOR is: identity, thesis, authorities, relationships, and
  the 2026-04-10 manhattan-recovery realignment event.
